Access Modifiers --- > specifies the accessibility or scope of a field, method, constructor, or class.

1) Private
2) Default
3) Protected
4) Public



-Private---> Only within the class
-Default --> If we don't specify any access modifiers it will be treated as a default.(Accessibility only within the package)
			 Default is not accessible outside of the pacakge.

-Protected ----> Accessible within the package and outside of the package but through Inheritance.
-Public ----> It can be accessed anywhere



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Access Modifier 				Within the class 				Within the package 						Outside the package
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Private 							Yes									NO										NO

Default								Yes									Yes										NO

Protected							Yes									Yes							Yes( but with Inheritance)

Public 								YES									YES										YES

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


















